[SN]TITLE[SN]
#Mysportmovie - The best of your film posters from BBC Sportsday debate

[SN]FIRST-SENTENCE[SN]
The daily BBC Sportsday debate started innocently enough.

[SN]RESTBODY[SN]
We asked you: if you were a Hollywood director, what sporting episode would you make into a movie and why?
The discussion stems from Wednesday's BBC Radio 5 live Sport special on Leicester City's remarkable season in the Premier League, and how one Hollywood producer is planning to make a film about the rise of striker Jamie Vardy.
Twitter users started getting their creative juices flowing and began sending in mocked-up film posters.
Things escalated quickly...
